<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="17Dec1923"><font color="red">17 December 1923</font> <i>Letters I</i> (to Harriet Weaver): I enclose a long piece with the final script. The others [earlier drafts] are in a book [MS 47471b], all scrawled over in red pencil. I shall send it when it is full. To do so now would mean tearing out the leaves. I hope this extract will give you some pleasure in the reading.  &hellip; These last weeks have been really dreadful and we seem to be sinking deeper into the morass. I stopped work in despair for a week and then started again night and day. I work like a person who is stunned. I cannot imagine any position more grotesque  &hellip; </div>
